{DIALOGUE}: I'm Dorothy Harris.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: Well, now we ain't strangers anymore.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bus driver smiles as Forrest steps up into the bus.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest steps up onto the bus.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mrs. Gump waves to Forrest as the bus drives away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest begins to walk down the aisle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TWO YOUNG BOYS look up from the seat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOY #1
{DIALOGUE}: This seat's taken.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOY #2
{DIALOGUE}: It's taken!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest looks around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A larger girl slides over so Forrest can't sit next to her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She shakes her head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest looks to the other side where a boy sits alone on a larger seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They boy glares up at Forrest.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOY #3
{DIALOGUE}: You can't sit here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: You know, it's funny what a young man recollects.
{DIALOGUE}: 'Cause I don't remember being born.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SAVANNAH/BUS BENCH - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest continues talking as he sits on the bus bench.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I, I..
{DIALOGUE}: don't recall what I got for my first Christmas and I don't know when I went on my first outdoor picnic.
{DIALOGUE}: But, I do remember the first time I heard the sweetiest voice...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BUS - MORNING (1954)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Young Forrest is still standing in the aisle on the bus.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...in the wide world.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIRL
{DIALOGUE}: You can sit here if you want.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest looks back at JENNY CURRAN, a young girl about Forrest's age.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I had never seen anything so beautiful in my life.
{DIALOGUE}: She was like an angel.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JENNY
{DIALOGUE}: Well, are you gonna sit down, or aren't ya?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest sits down next to Jenny.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JENNY
{DIALOGUE}: What's wrong with your legs?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: Um, nothing at all, thank you.
{DIALOGUE}: My legs are just fine and dandy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I just sat next to her on that bus and had conversation all the way to school.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JENNY
{DIALOGUE}: Then why do you have those shoes on?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: My momma said my back's crooked like a question mark.
{DIALOGUE}: These are going to make me as straight as an arrow.
{DIALOGUE}: They're my magic shoes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: And next to Momma, no one ever talked to me or asked me questions.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JENNY
{DIALOGUE}: Are you stupid or something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: Mommy says stupid is as stupid does.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jenny puts her hand out toward Forrest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest reaches over and shakes her hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JENNY
{DIALOGUE}: I'm Jenny.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: I'm Forrest Gump.
{DIALOGUE}: Forrest Gump.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: From that day on, we was always together.
{DIALOGUE}: Jenny and me was like peas and carrots.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. OAK TREE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Young Jenny and Forrest run toward a large oak tree.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: She taught me how to climb...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jenny sits on a large branch and calls down to Forrest.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JENNY
{DIALOGUE}: Come on, Forrest, you can do it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest dangles from the branch.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...I showed her how to dangle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jenny and Forrest sit on a tree branch and read.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: "...a good little monkey and..."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: She helped me to learn how to read.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest hangs upside down from a branch and swings back and forth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest's braces are wedged in the tree.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: And I showed her to swing.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. OAK TREE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The silhouete of the oak tree, Jenny and Forrest as they sit on a branch.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Sometimes we'd just sit out and wait for the stars.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
