{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOVERNOR WALLACE
{DIALOGUE}: We must have no violence today, or any other day, because these National Guardsmen are here today as Federal Soldiers for Alabamans.
{DIALOGUE}: And they live within our borders and they are all our brothers.
{DIALOGUE}: We are winning in this fight because we are awakening the American people to the dangers that we have spoken about so many times, just so evident today, the trend toward military dictatorship in this country.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. UNIVERSITY OF ALABAMA
