{DIALOGUE}: Her dream had come true.
{DIALOGUE}: She was a folk singer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JENNY
{META_DATA}: (sings)
{DIALOGUE}: "Yes, how many times must the cannonballs fly before they're forever banned."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #1
{DIALOGUE}: You gotta lose the guitar, darling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #2
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, come on, baby.
{DIALOGUE}: Shake it up.
{DIALOGUE}: Shake it up now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #3
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, somebody ought to get her a harmonica.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men laugh.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JENNY
