{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: No, we are not relations, sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LT. DAN
{DIALOGUE}: Look, it's pretty basic here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lt. Dan starts to walk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bubba and Forrest grab their gear and follow him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LT. DAN
{DIALOGUE}: You stick with me, you learn from the guys who been in country awhile, you'll be right.
{DIALOGUE}: There is one item of G.I. gear that can be the difference between a live grunt and a dead grunt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lt. Dan stops and looks at the boys.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LT. DAN
{DIALOGUE}: Socks, cushion, sole, O.D. green.
{DIALOGUE}: Try and keep your feet dry when we're out humpin'.
{DIALOGUE}: I want you boys to remember to change your socks wherever we stop.
{DIALOGUE}: The Mekong will eat a grunt's feet right off his legs.
