{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The policeman pulls the patch cords out of the audio board.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest's amplified voice becomes inaudible.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest continues to speak into the microphone, even though no one can hear what he is saying.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hilary looks over and notices the policeman.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hilary rushes over toward the audio board, pushes the policeman away and grabs his night stick.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another protester grabs the policeman and pulls him away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: POLICEMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, what the hell are you doing?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HILARY
{DIALOGUE}: I'll beat your head in, you goddamned oinker!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Isabel, Hilary and another protester try to plug the tangled mess of wires back into the audio board.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ISABEL
{DIALOGUE}: Christ, what'd they do with this?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest continues to speak into the microphone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The crowd grows restless.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CROWD
{DIALOGUE}: We can't hear you!
{DIALOGUE}: We can't hear anything!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HILARY
{DIALOGUE}: This one!
{DIALOGUE}: This one!
{DIALOGUE}: Give me that!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hilary plugs in the right patch cord.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HILARY
{DIALOGUE}: That's it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: ...and that's all I have to say about that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest looks at the massive crowd.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are silent.
