{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest flails his arms as he swims up to the dock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lt. Dan waits for Forrest, smoking a cigar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest climbs up a ladder onto the dock.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: Lieutenant Dan, what are you doing here?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LT. DAN
{DIALOGUE}: Well, I thought I'd try out my sea legs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: Well, you ain't got no legs, Lieutenant Dan.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LT. DAN
{DIALOGUE}: Well, well, Captain Forrest Gump.
{DIALOGUE}: I had to see this for myself.
{DIALOGUE}: And I told you if you were ever a shrimp boat captain, that I'd be your first mate.
{DIALOGUE}: Well, here I am.
{DIALOGUE}: I am a man of my word.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: Okay.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest shakes Lt. Dan's hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LT. DAN
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, but don't you be thinking that I'm gonna be calling you sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: No, sir.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest's boat glides, crushing a dock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest and Lt. Dan look at it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: That's my boat.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BAYOU LA BATRE WATERS - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest's shrimping boat is alone on the gulf waters.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LT. DAN
