{DIALOGUE}: Though I think he left the praying up to me.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BOAT - ANOTHER DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A catch of junk is dumped onto the deck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lt. Dan lowers himself from the rigging.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: No shrimp.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LT. DAN
{DIALOGUE}: Where the hell's this God of yours?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The wind begins to blow strong.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: It's funny Lieutenant Dan said that, 'cause right then, God showed up.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BOAT - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Water sprays on deck during a hurricane.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lt. Dan on the rigging, shouts and shakes his fist as he is pelted by wind and rain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LT. DAN
{DIALOGUE}: You'll never sink this boat!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Now me, I was scared.
{DIALOGUE}: But Lieutenant Dan, he was mad.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LT. DAN
{DIALOGUE}: Come on!
{DIALOGUE}: You call this a storm?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest slides back and forth as he attempts to steer the boat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LT. DAN
{DIALOGUE}: Blow, you son-of-a-bitch!
{DIALOGUE}: Blow!
{DIALOGUE}: It's time for a showdown!
{DIALOGUE}: You and me.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm right here.
{DIALOGUE}: Come and get me!
{DIALOGUE}: You'll never sink this boat!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GUMP HOUSE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An ANCHORMAN over TV, is standing in front of a pier.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANCHORMAN
{META_DATA}: (over television)
{DIALOGUE}: Hurricane Carmen came through here yesterday...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BAYOU DOCKS - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The anchorman is standing in front of the ruined pier and boats.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANCHORMAN
{DIALOGUE}: ...destroying nearly everything in its path.
{DIALOGUE}: And as in other towns up and down the coast, Bayou La Batre's entire shrimping industry...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GUMP HOUSE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANCHORMAN
{DIALOGUE}: ...has fallen victim to Carmen and has been left in utter ruin.
{DIALOGUE}: Speaking with local officials, this reporter has learned, in fact, only one shrimping boat actually survived the storm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest's boat comes down the river.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MRS. GUMP
{DIALOGUE}: Louise.
{DIALOGUE}: Louise, there's Forrest!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: After that, shrimpin' was easy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FORREST'S BOAT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lt. Dan and Forrest empty their net.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A huge catch of shrimp falls onto the deck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lt. Dan opens another big catch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another catch drops open on top of yet another huge catch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest and Lt. Dan smile.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: And since people still needed them shrimps for shrimp cocktails and barbecues and all...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BUS STOP - PRESENT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man sitting on the bench listens to Forrest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An ELDERLY WOMAN sits next to the man.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: ...and we were the only boat left standing "Bubba-Gump" shrimp's what they got.
