{DIALOGUE}: ...it gave people hope.
{DIALOGUE}: Now... Now, I don't know anything about that, but...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest and his followers job through a small town.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A man runs up and talks to Forrest.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Some of those people asked me if I could help them out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGING HIPPIE
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, man, hey, listen.
{DIALOGUE}: I was wondering if you might help me, huh?
{DIALOGUE}: Listen, I'm in the bumper sticker business and I've been trying to think up a good slogan.
{DIALOGUE}: And since you have been such a big inspiration to the people around here, I thought you might be able to help me jump into... Whoa!
{DIALOGUE}: Man, you just ran through a big pile of dogshit!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hippie jumps over the "dogshit" as he runs along Forrest.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: It happens.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGING HIPPIE
{DIALOGUE}: What, shit?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST
{DIALOGUE}: Sometimes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hippie stops to ponder this profound thought.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: And some years later I heard that fella did come up with a bumper sticker slogan...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bumper sticker reads "Shit Happens."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...and he make a lot of money off of it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The truck with the bumper sticker drives into an intersection.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It collides with a car.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. TRUCK STOP
