{CHARACTER_NAME}: SCHOOLD BUS DRIVER
{DIALOGUE}: You understand this is the bus to school now, don't you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FORREST JR.
{DIALOGUE}: Of course, and you're Dorothy Harris and I'm Forrest Gump.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest Jr. looks over and waves to his father.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest nods approvingly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest Jr. gets on the bus.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bus pulls away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest stands next to the mailbox.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest sits down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The camera cranes down, revealing the feather as it lies at Forrest's feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A gust of wind picks the feather up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The feather floats up into the air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Forrest sits at the side of the road.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The feather floats higher into the air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The feather soars up into the sky and travels up and down, then covers the camera lens.
{META_DATA}: THE END
